pro_sql_19

Operators

The WHERE clause can be combined with AND, OR, and NOT SQL operators.

Using the AND operator:
SELECT * FROM movies WHERE release_year>2010 AND genre='Comedy';

This query will select all rows from the movies table where the release_year is after 2010 and the genre is Comedy.

Using the OR operator:

SELECT * FROM movies WHERE releas_year>2010 OR genre = 'Comedy';

This query will select all rows from the movies table where the release year is after 2010 or the genre is Comedy.

Using the NOT operator:
SELECT * FROM movies WHERE NOTgenre = 'Comedy';

This query will select all rows from the movies table where the genre is not Comedy.
